    "Within this structure, patients and caregivers may become inadequately informed participants in the development of AI products, without ethical oversight from IRBs or Data and Safety Monitoring Boards 34.",
    "AI medical applications and tools present significant potential benefits as well as risks that extend beyond operational and administrative efficiencies.",
    "The widespread integration of these technologies into healthcare systems demands rigorous transparency and detailed disclosures to patients and clinicians regarding the data being collected, its intended use, and how it will be managed and shared.",
    "A recent class action lawsuit was filed against Humana for allegedly using the AI model NHPredict to wrongfully deny necessary care to Medicare Advantage patients 35.",
    "Another lawsuit claims that United Healthcare used the same model to override clinicians' medical determinations, leading to the rejection of valid claims 36."
